line_1: Here pale and trembling, in the dust o'erturn'd,
line_2: With chains dishonour'd, and by eunuchs spurn'd,

line_1: He, who had often, and alone, o'erturn'd
line_2: Witlings, and sophists, when his fury burn'd,

line_1: Of sense by sorrow's sway o'erturned.
line_2: When I could o'er thy grief have mourned,

line_1: Where now the sacred altar lies o'erturn'd!
line_2: Bowing to saints on every side inurn'd,
E'er see, — howe'er th' accursed crime were mourn'd,
